oai_dc:dc.dc:title: NON-LINEAR WAVE-CURRENT INTERACTIONS IN THE SWADE RESEARCH PROGRAM
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Kjeldsen, S.P.
Graber, H.C.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: nonlinear wave
wave/current interaction
Swade research program
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This publication gives an introduction to the SWADE experimental programme. It presents examples of results of directional ocean wave spectra in polar format obtained by the third generation met/ocean buoy WAVESCAN. Then focus is made on a new algorithm "CUWA" that simulates non-linear Stokes waves propagating through regions of strong surface current.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 23 (1992): Proceedings of 23rd Conference on Coastal Engineering, Venice, Italy, 1992.
